Congregation members of the Enlightened Christian Gathering Church (ECG) have started to gather outside the Pretoria Magistrate’s Court where their pastor Shepherd Bushiri and his wife Mary Bushiri are due to appear on Wednesday morning. The pastor handed himself over to police in Silverton, Pretoria while his wife was arrested at her residence in Sandton, north of Johannesburg on Tuesday.  It’s gonna be a great year#Bushiri pic.twitter.com/eO7dpwnnnG — AbdulRazziq (@Abdul80233125) October 20, 2020  The couple is accused of fraud and money laundering totalling R102 million, along with two other suspects who were arrested in Johannesburg at the weekend. The other two, Willah Mudolo and Zethu Mudolo, have already appeared in the same court and are expected to apply for bail on the 30th of October. The video below, is reporting on Bushiri’s July court appearance: 